GeneralExplanationGrp.MediumExplanationTxt: MFA IS AN ORGANIZATION COMMITTED TO TEACHERS. OUR GOAL IS TO INSPIRE OUTSTANDING PROFESSIONALS SO THEY CONTINUE TEACHING AND TO AMPLIFY THEIR IMPACT THROUGHOUT THEIR CAREERS. WE OFFER FOUR-YEAR FELLOWSHIPS FOR ACCOMPLISHED NYC PUBLIC SCHOOL MATHEMATICS AND SCIENCE TEACHERS, CREATING OPPORTUNITIES FOR THEIR PROFESSIONAL AND INTELLECTUAL GROWTH. OUR FELLOWSHIPS PROVIDE A LARGE ARRAY OF PROFESSIONAL LEARNING OPPORTUNITIES --WORKSHOPS, MINI-COURSES, AND SEMINARS -- BRINGING TEACHERS TOGETHER IN A COMMUNITY OF EXPERTS WHO SHARE A PASSION FOR MATHEMATICS AND SCIENCE. WE BELIEVE PARTICIPATION IN A PROFESSIONAL COMMUNITY IS CRITICAL TO SUSTAIN TEACHERS IN THEIR CAREERS. THROUGH OUR FELLOWSHIPS, MFA TEACHERS DEEPEN THEIR OWN CONTENT KNOWLEDGE, REFINE AND EXPAND THEIR SKILLS AS PEDAGOGUES, AND EXAMINE THE BEST WAYS TO TEACH EVERY STUDENT. TEACHERS IN OUR FELLOWSHIPS ARE IMPRESSIVE PROFESSIONALS. WE ELEVATE THEIR ACHIEVEMENTS TO BUILD THE RESPECT, TRUST, AND RECOGNITION THEY DESERVE. WE PROVIDE STIPENDS TO TEACHERS TO COMPENSATE THEM FOR THEIR WORK IN THE COMMUNITY. WE HONOR THEM IN A VARIETY OF WAYS. WE OFFER THEM OPPORTUNITIES TO SHARE THEIR VOICES BOTH LOCALLY AND NATIONALLY. IN THIS WAY, WE CELEBRATE NOT ONLY OUR TEACHERS BUT THE TEACHING PROFESSION.

GeneralExplanationGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990-PF, PART VIII-A - ACTIVITY DESCRIPTION: RECRUITMENT AND SELECTION
GeneralExplanationGrp.MediumExplanationTxt: MATH FOR AMERICA RECRUITS TALENTED INDIVIDUALS TO APPLY FOR THE FELLOWSHIP PROGRAMS. THE RECRUITMENT AND SELECTION PROCESS CONSISTS OF ATTENDING CAMPUS RECRUITMENT EVENTS, ADVERTISING, PROCESSING APPLICATIONS AND CONDUCTING INTERVIEW SESSIONS. THESE THINGS ELEVATE THE TEACHING PROFESSION ALL BY THEMSELVES.

OUR FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM IS BASED ON SPECIFIC VALUES, WHICH WE SEE AS KEY TO IMPROVING THE TEACHING PROFESSION IN GENERAL. WE BROADLY ADVOCATE FOR THESE VALUES. TEACHING IS A TRUE PROFESSION. IT IS THE PROFESSION THAT MAKES ALL OTHER PROFESSIONS POSSIBLE. A LIFE-LONG TEACHING CAREER IS A PRESTIGIOUS ACCOMPLISHMENT. GREAT TEACHERS ARE ALWAYS LEARNING. TEACHER QUALITY IS THE FOUNDATION FOR STUDENT SUCCESS, AND THE BEST TEACHERS STRIVE TO GROW CONTINUALLY IN THREE AREAS: -DEPTH OF CONTENT KNOWLEDGE -THEIR EXPERTISE IN THE CRAFT OF TEACHING -THEIR ABILITY TO KNOW AND TO TEACH EVERY STUDENT IN THEIR CLASSROOMS. EXCELLENCE COMES OUT OF DEEP COLLABORATION AND ONGOING GROWTH. WHEN EXCELLENT TEACHERS COME TOGETHER, WITH INTENTION, OVER A SUSTAINED PERIOD, THEY LEARN FROM EACH OTHER, INNOVATE, AND BRING NEW IDEAS TO THEIR CLASSROOMS. ACCOMPLISHED TEACHERS ARE TRUSTED AS PROFESSIONALS. WE NOT ONLY RESPECT TEACHERS, WE TRUST THEM TO CURATE THEIR OWN PROFESSIONAL LEARNING GOALS. OUTSTANDING TEACHERS KNOW THEIR STUDENTS BEST AND KNOW WHAT THEY NEED TO GROW AS PROFESSIONALS. HONORING GREATNESS ELEVATES THE PROFESSION. WHEN WE CELEBRATE, RECOGNIZE, AND ADVOCATE FOR TEACHERS, WE ELEVATE THE PROFESSION, ENCOURAGING THE BEST TEACHERS TO CREATE LIFE-LONG, MEANINGFUL CAREERS IN THE CLASSROOM AND ATTRACTING THE BEST POSSIBLE CANDIDATES TO THE PROFESSION. ABOVE ALL, WE WORK TO CHANGE THE WAY WE TALK ABOUT TEACHERS AND TEACHING.

WE ALSO ENCOURAGE AND PROVIDE AID TO PROGRAMS SIMILAR TO THE MFA FELLOWSHIP MODEL ELSEWHERE IN OTHER LOCATIONS. WE BELIEVE THE PRINCIPLES THAT UNDERLIE MFA ARE ESSENTIAL TO RETAIN AND ATTRACT THE VERY BEST MATHEMATICS AND SCIENCE TEACHERS. WE ADVOCATE FOR ALL TEACHERS, TO BE RESPECTED AND TRUSTED AS PROFESSIONALS AND TO HAVE ACCESS TO A MEANINGFUL PROFESSIONAL COMMUNITY WHERE THEIR VOICES ARE HEARD. WE WANT OUR FELLOWSHIPS TO CHANGE THE WAY WE THINK ABOUT TEACHING IN AMERICA.
